development the environment and enhancing the quality of life for citizens across the  communities we serve whether it’s building homes for the less fortunate providing support for children to explore their curiosity for science and technology or assisting senior citizens with yard cleanup im and our  employees enjoy giving back to the communities where we live and work in 0 im contributed nearly  to nonprofit and economic development agencies in addition the american electric power foundation contributed more than  to nonprofit agencies in our service territory in this report you will see a list of some of the agencies that received contributions from indiana michigan power and the american electric power foundation thank you for the opportunity to serve you and support the people and organizations that make our communities great places to live sincerely toby thomas president and chief operating officer indiana michigan power indiana contributions michigan contributions indiana michigan power aep ohioaep texasappalachian powerindiana michigan powerkentucky powerpublic service company of oklahomasouthwestern electric power company back to the top home investors news releases  email alerts events presentations  webcasts sec filings  other financial reports current regulatory activity corporate leaders  governance buy and manage aep stock stock history  dividends shareholder contact  faqs newsroom corporate news releases media relations contacts regional utility news facts  leadership other industry resources subscribe to news alerts financialinvestors information environment corporate accountability report climate change emissions  compliance environmental news conservation  outdoor recreation falconcam community aep foundation corporate giving guidelines community affairs  economic development safety  health for teachers  students conservation  outdoor recreation community connections report careers current job openings college coops  internships taking an employmen